<http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.5390.1.1>
    dc:creator "Bertani, Rogério" ;
    dc:date "2023" ;
    dc:title "Taxonomic revision and cladistic analysis of Lasiodora C. L. Koch, 1850 (Araneae, Theraphosidae) with notes on related genera" ;
    bibo:endPage "116" ;
    bibo:issue "1" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2023-12-27" ;
    bibo:startPage "1" ;
    bibo:volume "5390" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10434518>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10434602>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10434604>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10434606>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10434610>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10434616> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10434518>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1–2. 1, reproduction of Eckhout’s 1643 painting showing an indigenous Brazilian man with flora and fauna elements found in the region now known as state of Pernambuco, Brazil. A large theraphosid can be seen close to the man’s right foot. 2, Detail of the spider. This is the second oldest known image of a theraphosid from the New World." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10434518/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10434602>
    dc:description "FIGURES 125─130. Lasiodora parahybana Mello-Leitão, 1917. (125–129) male (MNRJ 7761). (125–127) left palp bulb. 125, retrolateral. 126, prolateral. 127, dorsal. (128─129) left tibial apophysis. 128, ventral. 129, prolateral. 130, female (MZUSP 78869), spermathecae. Scale bar = 1mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10434602/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10434604>
    dc:description "FIGURES 131─135. Lasiodora parahybana Mello-Leitão, 1917, male (MNRJ 7761), stridulatory apparatus. (131─132) left maxilla, retrolateral. 131, general view. 132, detail of spiniform setae on upper area. (133─135) left coxa I, prolateral. 133, general view. 134, detail of stridulatory setae. 135, detail of area below suture. Scale bar = 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10434604/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10434606>
    dc:description "FIGURES 136─140. Lasiodora parahybana Mello-Leitão, 1917, female (MZUSP 78869), stridulatory apparatus. (136─137) left maxilla, retrolateral. 136, general view. 137, detail of spiniform setae on upper area. (138─140) left coxa I, prolateral. 138, general view. 139, detail of stridulatory setae. 140, detail of area below suture. Scale bar = 1mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10434606/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10434610>
    dc:description "FIGURES 147─150. Lasiodora acanthognatha Mello-Leitão, 1921, holotype immature male (MNRJ 47/798). 147, left coxa I, prolateral. 148, left maxilla, retrolateral. (149─150) chelicerae. 149, dorsal. 150, ventral. Scale bar = 1mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10434610/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10434616>
    dc:description "FIGURES 163─164. Maps showing records of Lasiodora parahybana Mello-Leitão, 1917 in northeastern Brazil. 163, relief. 164, biomes. Forested areas of Fig. 164 are in green shades, on east (Brazilian Atlantic Forest) and on west (Amazon). Brown areas are of Cerrado; and pinkish, Caatinga." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10434616/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

